---

tbs olive oil
½ unit onion
1 unit parsnip
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 clove garlic
½ unit lemon
1 bunch spring onion
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 sachet smoked paprika
1 tsp brown sugar
¼ tsp salt
1 packet chicken breast
20 g butter
¾ cup water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet couscous
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Slice the red onion (see ingredients list) into 2cm chunks. Cut the parsnip (unpeeled) into 1cm chunks. Place the peeled & chopped pumpkin, onion and parsnip on an oven tray lined with baking paper. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat and roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

TIP: Cut the veggies to size so they cook in time.
TIP: If your oven tray looks crowded, separate across two oven trays!

While the veggies are roasting, finely chop the garlic. Zest the lemon to get a pinch, then slice in half. Thinly slice the spring onion. Roughly chop the baby spinach leaves. In a large bowl, combine the smoked paprika, brown sugar, the salt, a good squeeze of lemon juice and a generous drizzle of olive oil. Add the chicken breast and toss to coat. Set aside.

Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat. When the pan is hot, add the chicken and cook until golden, 2-3 minutes each side. Transfer the chicken to a second oven tray lined with baking paper and bake until cooked through, 8-12 minutes. Let the chicken rest for 5 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

While the chicken is cooking, melt the butter in a medium saucepan over a medium-high heat. Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Add the water and chicken-style stock powder and bring to the boil. Add the couscous and stir to combine, then cover with a lid and remove from the heat. Set aside until all the water is absorbed, 5 minutes, then fluff up with a fork. Add the roasted veggies, baby spinach, lemon zest and spring onion (reserve a little for garnish) and stir to combine. Season to taste.

In a small bowl, combine the yoghurt and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper.

Thickly slice the chicken. Divide the roast veggie couscous between plates and top with the smokey chicken, spooning any resting juices over the chicken. Drizzle with the lemon yoghurt and garnish with the reserved spring onion.